## üéØ Common Scenarios

### Scenario 1: "I just updated background.js with new features"
**Solution:** Level 4 (Full Remove/Reload)
**Why:** First deployment of service worker changes REQUIRES full reload

### Scenario 2: "Extension already has new code, need to test reload feature"
**Solution:** Level 2 or 3 (API Reload or Force Reload)
**Why:** Code already loaded, just testing runtime behavior

### Scenario 3: "Changed popup.html styling"
**Solution:** Level 1 (Soft Reload)
**Why:** HTML/CSS doesn't need service worker restart

### Scenario 4: "Tests failing with 'No extensions connected'"
**Solution:** Level 4 (Full Remove/Reload)
**Why:** Server rejecting old registration format

### Scenario 5: "Automated testing workflow"
**Solution:** Level 3 (Force Reload) in test setup
**Why:** Fast, automated, programmatic

